Dear ! I was so glad to have him back that I 
was just as near happy as a person could be that 
was up in the air that way with a deranged man. 
You can't land a balloon in the dark, and so I 
hoped it would keep on raining, for I did n't 
want Tom to go meddling any more and make 
us so awful uncomfortable. Well, I got my 
wish. It drizzled and drizzled along the rest of 
the night, which was n't long, though it did seem 
so; and at daybreak it cleared, and the world 
looked mighty soft and gray and pretty, and the 
