horses and cattle standing sober and thinking. 
Next, the sun come a-blazing up gay and splen- 
did, and then we began to feel rusty and stretchy, 
and first we knowed we was all asleep. 



CHAPTER IIL 

TOM EXPLAINS. 

We went to sleep about four o'clock, and woke 
up about eight. The professor was setting- back 
there at his end, looking glum. He pitched us 
