five such jumps every second, which is fifteen 
hundred times his own length. Well, suppose a 
man could go fifteen hundred times his own 
length in a second — say, a mile and a half. It 's 



TOM RESPECTS THE FLEA. 103 

ninety miles a minute; it 's considerable more 
than five thousand miles an hour. Where 's 
your man nozu .^— yes, and your bird, and your 
