stretched out on the lockers reading, sometimes 
taking a nap. 

It did n't seem like we was the same lot that 
was in such a state to find land and git ashore, 
but it was. But we had got over that — clean 
over it. We was used to the balloon, now, and 
not afraid any more, and did n't want to be any- 
wheres else. Why, it seemed just like home ; it 
'most seemed as if I had been born and raised 
