Well, up in a balloon there ain't any of that, 
and it 's the darlingest place there is. 

We had supper, and that night was one of the 
prettiest nights I ever see. The moon made it 
just like daylight, only a heap softer ; and once 
we see a lion standing all alone by himself, just 
all alone on the earth, it seemed like, and his 
shadder laid on the sand by him like a puddle 
of ink. That 's the kind of moonlight to have. 

Mainly we laid on our backs and talked ; we 



no  

did n't want to go to sleep. Tom said we was 
