seemed foolish to sleep and not make the most 
of it, I might n't ever have such a chance again. 

We went a-fishing again in the early dawn, 
and then lazied around all day in the deep shade 
on an island, taking turn about to watch and 
see that none of the animals come a-snooping 
around there after erronorts for dinner. We 



