was n't fitten' for a humble poor nigger to come 
any other way where such men had been as 
Moses and Joseph and Pharaoh and the other 
prophets. He was a Presbyterian, and had a 
most deep respect for Moses which was a Pres- 



l86  

byterian too, he said. He was all stirred up, 
